                                        <a class="collapsed" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseTwo" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseTwo">
                                            What is Anatomy of Spinal Stenosis? Lumbar Canal Stenosis? Lumbar Spinal Stenosis?
                                        </a>
                                    </h4>
                                </div>
                                <div id="collapseTwo" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="headingTwo">
                                    <div class="panel-body">
                                        <div class="cliclskil1">
                                            <ul>
                                                <li><img src="img/founder_li_icon.png" class="wow flipInX animated animated" data-wow-iteration="infinite" alt="pic" style="visibility: visible; animation-iteration-count: infinite; animation-name: flipInX;">Spinal stenosis means Narrowing of space for nerves in the spine due to compression.</li>
                                                <li><img src="img/founder_li_icon.png" class="wow flipInX animated animated" data-wow-iteration="infinite" alt="pic" style="visibility: visible; animation-iteration-count: infinite; animation-name: flipInX;">When the disc or cushion bulges and degeneration (wear and tear) of facet joints (joints in the spine) protrude into the spinal canal causing compression of the nerve then its called Spinal Stenosis.</li>
                                            </ul>
                                            <p class="mt-2"><b>Lumbar Canal Stenosis, Lumbar Spinal Stenosis:</b></p>
                                            <p>Degeneration of joints and disc bulge into the canal of nerves results in reduced space for nerves into the canal of nerves resulting in a spinal stenosis. Compression of nerve results in back pain, buttock pain, leg pain, leg numbness or buttock pain traveling down the leg and patients complains of pain in leg with numbness and difficulty in walking. This pain in legs with numbness in leg and heaviness in leg increase during walking and is called claudication.</p>
                                            <img class="serv_img mt-2" src="img/capture10.png">
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
