                                                <li><img src="img/founder_li_icon.png" class="wow flipInX animated animated" data-wow-iteration="infinite" alt="pic" style="visibility: visible; animation-iteration-count: infinite; animation-name: flipInX;">Conventionally done spine surgery has demerits and involves retraction of muscles and stripping of muscles with the removal of bone from spine although extremely safe, patients who undergo open spine surgery may require a longer hospitalization due to relatively higher post-operative pain, blood loss, infection chances and prolonged rehabilitation period.</li>
                                                <li><img src="img/founder_li_icon.png" class="wow flipInX animated animated" data-wow-iteration="infinite" alt="pic" style="visibility: visible; animation-iteration-count: infinite; animation-name: flipInX;">Whereas Minimal Invasive Spine Surgery not only aims at giving the benefits of open surgery but also cuts down the demerits of open spine surgery. Minimal Invasive Spine Surgery or keyhole spine surgery aims at smaller incisions, less blood loss, no postoperative pain, shorter hospitalization, no infection, early rehabilitation and returns to work . also it has a minimal scar which is cosmetically better.</li>
                                                <li><img src="img/founder_li_icon.png" class="wow flipInX animated animated" data-wow-iteration="infinite" alt="pic" style="visibility: visible; animation-iteration-count: infinite; animation-name: flipInX;">The keyhole surgery technique or minimally invasive surgery for spinal surgery can be safely and easily performed with the help of microscope or endoscope and so are called microscopic spine surgery or endoscopic spine surgery. this technique has been successfully used to treat slip disc/herniated disc/sciatica/spinal stenosis/spinal instability/spondylolisthesis, spinal fractures etc.</li>
                                            </ul>
